metadata.description:
My very first house track, dated pre-Soulection, that started my journey and transition from mere bedroom/dorm room beatmaker fawning over FlyLo's "Reset" EP, to electronic music producer trying expand his horizon past the then-overly popular J Dilla aesthetic, aspiring to Daft Punk more than Slum Village (the funny part being my favorite track the time was a Dilla/Slum Village remix of "Aerodynamic", lol).

That was the scene that set up this track, which I've revamped countless times after to feature in mixes everywhere, on Soulection, on BBC Radio 1, but never officially released; until now, of course.

Though this is a rare one, I want as many people as possible to listen to it AND have a chance to get what is possibly, literally my rarest gem drop yet out of my vault. This one is just pure vibes, but I meant it to really just take you somewhere, but nowhere in particular either; distanced from this reality into another, if that's what calls to you...
metadata.name: Distanced #1
metadata.title: Distanced
